FBIS3-57050 "drsov015_d_94007" FBIS-SOV-94-015 Document Type:Daily Report 25 Jan 1994 Regional Affairs Sobchak: Petersburg To Pursue Autonomous Policy LD2101192294 Moscow Radio Rossii Network in Russian 1800 GMT 21 Jan 94 LD2101192294 Moscow Radio Rossii Network Language: Russian Article Type:BFN [Text] Anatoliy Sobchak told journalists today that St. Petersburg will defend its rights as a subject of the Federation and pursue an autonomous policy, irrespective of what is happening in the Russian parliament, in particular continue with privatization and trying attract foreign banks and investments into the city. St. Petersburg's mayor believes that the Russian Government has become economically disorientated. In Sobchak's view, in the conditions of the market it must, in the first place, work on the finance-credit system and the regulation of the cost of goods transportation inside Russia.
